      "id": "pet-lionking-006",
      "exam": "PET",
      "part": "reading",
      "level": "B1",
      "title": "Remember Who You Are",
      "text": "Rafiki, the wise old baboon, had sensed that Simba was alive. He travelled to the jungle and found Simba sitting alone. Rafiki told Simba that his father was not truly gone — he lived on in Simba himself. He led Simba through the jungle to a pool of water. \"Look inside,\" Rafiki said. Simba looked at his reflection but saw only himself. \"Look harder,\" Rafiki insisted. This time, Simba saw his father's face staring back at him. Mufasa was a part of him. Then, in the clouds above, Mufasa's spirit appeared as a great vision. \"Simba,\" the voice said, \"you have forgotten me. You have forgotten who you are and so forgotten me.\" Mufasa told Simba that he was his son and the one true king. \"Remember who you are,\" the voice said. \"You must take your place in the circle of life.\" The vision faded, but Simba was transformed. He finally understood. He could not run from his past anymore. He was the son of Mufasa, the rightful king of the Pride Lands. It was time to go home and face Scar. Rafiki gave Simba a light hit on the head with his stick. \"It doesn't matter. It's in the past,\" he laughed, and Simba understood.",
      "source": "Adapted from Disney's The Lion King (1994)",
      "sourcePath": "data/pet/The Lion King/006.md",
      "sectionKey": "reading-the-lion-king",
