      "id": "pet-lionking-007",
      "exam": "PET",
      "part": "reading",
      "level": "B1",
      "title": "Return to Pride Rock",
      "text": "Simba, Nala, Timon, and Pumbaa journeyed back to the Pride Lands. When Simba saw his home, his heart sank. The beautiful land he remembered was gone. It was grey, dry, and dead. The sky was dark with smoke, and no animals could be seen anywhere. Simba climbed Pride Rock, where Scar was ruling over what was left of the kingdom. Scar was shocked to see Simba alive. In front of all the lionesses, Scar accused Simba of being responsible for Mufasa's death, just as he had told him years ago. He backed Simba to the edge of the rock, ready to push him off. But then Scar made a mistake. He whispered to Simba, \"I killed Mufasa.\" Simba froze. The rage inside him burst out. He turned on Scar and forced him to tell the truth to everyone. The lionesses heard it, and a great battle broke out between Simba's allies and the hyenas. In the end, Simba cornered Scar at the top of Pride Rock. Scar begged for his life, blaming everything on the hyenas. But it was too late. The hyenas, who had heard Scar betray them, attacked him. Scar fell, and his rule was over.",
      "source": "Adapted from Disney's The Lion King (1994)",
