      "id": "pet-lionking-008",
      "exam": "PET",
      "part": "reading",
      "level": "B1",
      "title": "The Circle Continues",
      "text": "The rain began to fall. It was the first rain in years, and it washed away the dust and ash. Simba climbed to the top of Pride Rock and roared — a mighty roar that echoed across the savannah. The lionesses answered, and one by one, they followed their new king. Green returned to the Pride Lands. Animals came back, and life began again. Simba took his rightful place as king, with Nala by his side as queen. Timon and Pumbaa stayed close, proud of their friend. Soon, Rafiki appeared again at the top of Pride Rock, holding a new cub — Simba and Nala's baby. He lifted the tiny lion for all the animals to see, just as he had done with Simba years before. The circle of life continued, unbroken. Simba looked up at the stars. He knew his father was watching, proud of him at last. He had run from his past, but he had found the courage to face it. He was no longer a scared cub hiding in the jungle. He was King Simba, son of Mufasa, and the Pride Lands were alive once more.",
